    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All seven assessed credibility factors meet or exceed required levels for MRL 2. Six factors were scoped out as not applicable at this model risk level per ASME V&V 40-2018 Table 1. The CFD model is deemed sufficiently credible to support identification of worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for the Class II CPB device. The hemolysis prediction methodology referenced in the supporting literature (doi:10.1016/j.ymeth.2024.03.003) provides additional mechanistic justification for the power-law damage accumulation model employed.",
